    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Freddi</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2006/11/to-my-hearts-content/#comment-69528"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2018-06-27T15:19:50-04:00">Wednesday, June 27, 2018 at 3:19 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Although I&#8217;m a huge City Bakery fan and stop there at least once a week on my neighborhood rounds, I&#8217;d never tasted Maury&#8217;s Melted Chocolate Chip Cookies&#8212;&#8211;until last week.  I ran home and started googling similar recipes and found yours which I made today&#8230;. although it&#8217;s June in NYC,  it kinda looks like a baking day, grey and cloudy.  The cookies taste great but they don&#8217;t have that  CB shiny, crackly top.  Think it&#8217;s just that it&#8217;s a different recipe or what else could I have done wrong?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-69528' data-commentid="69528" data-postid="1575" data-belowelement="comment-69528" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Freddi" aria-label='Reply to Freddi'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-79987" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Audrey Goodrich</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2006/11/to-my-hearts-content/#comment-79987"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2020-10-06T13:27:06-04:00">Tuesday, October 6, 2020 at 1:27 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>These are the best cookies I have ever made and I&#8217;ve made a lot of cookies!  Sadly, City Bakery has closed so at least now I have this recipe to turn to!  THANK YOU!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-79987' data-commentid="79987" data-postid="1575" data-belowelement="comment-79987" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Audrey Goodrich" aria-label='Reply to Audrey Goodrich'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-85454" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Heather</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2006/11/to-my-hearts-content/#comment-85454"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2021-02-13T02:12:07-05:00">Saturday, February 13, 2021 at 2:12 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I found this recipe after the City Bakery branch in Brentwood, Los Angeles shut down because I missed the cookies so much. These are perfect! I make them for Christmas parties every year and everyone raves about them and wants to know who made them. Like, people I&#8217;ve never met will search the party trying to find the girl who made the chocolate cookies. They&#8217;re very much worth the work. Thanks for posting!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-85454' data-commentid="85454" data-postid="1575" data-belowelement="comment-85454" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Heather" aria-label='Reply to Heather'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-99924" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">P</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2006/11/to-my-hearts-content/#comment-99924"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2022-06-25T16:25:11-04:00">Saturday, June 25, 2022 at 4:25 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I remember the only time I tried this recipe I was with someone I deeply loved. August 2020  . Looking back now I feel the same pain of the &#8220;missing limb sydrom&#8221; .  I never made those cookies again but I come back to this post whenever I need to feel that same bittersweet feeling that , truth be told , never left me ever since .  Well , that feeling is here again tonight and here I am . Let&#8217;s roll</p>
    </div>

